1. A page with just one text box... That will ask the user for their policy number.

2. An error page, telling the user that the policy does not exist or has expired

3. A success page telling the user to check their registered email address for an OTP code. This same page will have a text box for them to input the sent OTP code.

4. A details page, showing a summary of the user's policy. This page will have a button called "Request Claim" at the bottom.

5. A form page for each of the forms I sent to you the other day... About 10 of them. Please don't forget to add the attachment UI as well, that is for forms that the users need to add an attachment while filling.

6.Then a final success page, after the user fills each form successfully.